Title: Object: The Flight into Egypt
Description: The Flight into Egypt, after Domenichino; the Holy Family approaching from the right, with a mule, on the bank of a river, with a ferry boat on the right, nearing the bank, a pyramid and small temple with a triangular pediment among the trees on the far bank and two figures on the shore; the etched state before engraving. 1766 Etching
Curator's comments: For the published state see 1869,0410.1037, and for a finished proof before letters see U,4.47.
Acquisition name: Bequeathed by: Clayton Mordaunt Cracherode (with his monogram and date 1780 on verso)
